{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd20990d5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3955"},"text":"§ 3955.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Termination of residential or motor vehicle leases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd20990d6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Termination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990d7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Termination by lessee","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The lessee on a lease described in subsection (b) may, at the lessee’s option, terminate the lease at any time after—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990d8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the lessee’s entry into military service;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990d9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the date of the lessee’s military orders described in paragraph (1)(B) or (2)(B) of subsection (b), as the case may be; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990da-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the date of the lessee’s stop movement order described in paragraph (1)(C) or (2)(C) of subsection (b), as the case may be.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990db-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Joint leases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A lessee’s termination of a lease pursuant to this subsection shall terminate any obligation a dependent of the lessee may have under the lease.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990dc-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Death of lessee","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The spouse or dependent of the lessee on a lease described in subsection (b) may terminate the lease during the one-year period beginning on the date of the death of the lessee, if the lessee dies while in military service or while performing full-time National Guard duty, active Guard and Reserve duty, or inactive-duty training (as such terms are defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101/d"},"text":"section 101(d) of title 10","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990dd-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Catastrophic injury or illness of lessee","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990de-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Termination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"If the lessee on a lease described in subsection (b) incurs a catastrophic injury or illness during a period of military service or while performing covered service, during the one-year period beginning on the date on which the lessee incurs such injury or illness—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990df-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the lessee may terminate the lease; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e0-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a lessee who lacks the mental capacity to contract or to manage his or her own affairs (including disbursement of funds without limitation) due to such injury or illness, the spouse or dependent of the lessee may terminate the lease.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e1-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this paragraph:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “catastrophic injury or illness” has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s439/g"},"text":"section 439(g) of title 37","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/a/4/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “covered service” means full-time National Guard duty, active Guard and Reserve duty, or inactive-duty training (as such terms are defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101/d"},"text":"section 101(d) of title 10","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e4-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Covered leases","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"This section applies to the following leases:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Leases of premises","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A lease of premises occupied, or intended to be occupied, by a servicemember or a servicemember’s dependents for a residential, professional, business, agricultural, or similar purpose if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the lease is executed by or on behalf of a person who thereafter and during the term of the lease enters military service;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the servicemember, while in military service, executes the lease and thereafter receives military orders for a permanent change of station or to deploy with a military unit, or as an individual in support of a military operation, for a period of not less than 90 days; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the servicemember, while in military service—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990e9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1/C/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" executes a lease upon receipt of military orders for a permanent change of station or to deploy with a military unit, or as an individual in support of a military operation, for a period of not less than 90 days; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ea-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/1/C/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" thereafter receives a stop movement order issued by the Secretary concerned in response to a local, national, or global emergency, effective for an indefinite period or for a period of not less than 30 days, which prevents the servicemember or servicemember’s dependents from occupying the lease for a residential, professional, business, agricultural, or similar purpose.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990eb-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Leases of motor vehicles","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A lease of a motor vehicle used, or intended to be used, by a servicemember or a servicemember’s dependents for personal or business transportation if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ec-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the lease is executed by or on behalf of a person who thereafter and during the term of the lease enters military service under a call or order specifying a period of not less than 180 days (or who enters military service under a call or order specifying a period of 180 days or less and who, without a break in service, receives orders extending the period of military service to a period of not less than 180 days);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ed-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the servicemember, while in military service, executes the lease and thereafter receives military orders—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ee-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" for a change of permanent station—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ef-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/B/i/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" from a location in the continental United States to a location outside the continental United States; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f0-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/B/i/II"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" from a location in a State outside the continental United States to any location outside that State; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f1-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to deploy with a military unit, or as an individual in support of a military operation, for a period of not less than 180 days; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the servicemember, while in military service—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/C/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" executes a lease upon receipt of military orders described in subparagraph (B); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f4-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/b/2/C/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" thereafter receives a stop movement order issued by the Secretary concerned in response to a local, national, or global emergency, effective for an indefinite period or for a period of not less than 30 days, which prevents the servicemember, or the servicemember’s dependents, from using the vehicle for personal or business transportation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Manner of termination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of a lease under subsection (a) is made—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by delivery by the lessee of written notice of such termination, and a copy of the servicemember’s military orders, to the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee), or to the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a lease of a motor vehicle, by return of the motor vehicle by the lessee to the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee), or to the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee), not later than 15 days after the date of the delivery of written notice under subparagraph (A).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990f9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Delivery of notice","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Delivery of notice under paragraph (1)(A) may be accomplished—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990fa-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by hand delivery;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990fb-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by private business carrier;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990fc-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" by placing the written notice in an envelope with sufficient postage and with return receipt requested, and addressed as designated by the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee) or to the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee), and depositing the written notice in the United States mails; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd20990fd-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" by electronic means, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990fe-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/D/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the direct delivery of material to an electronic address designated by the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee) or the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd20990ff-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/D/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the posting of material to a website or other internet or electronic-based information repository to which access has been granted to the lessee, the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee), or the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idd2099100-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/c/2/D/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other electronic means reasonably calculated to ensure actual receipt of the material by the lessor (or the lessor’s grantee) or the lessor’s agent (or the agent’s grantee).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd2099101-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Effective date of lease termination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099102-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Lease of premises","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099103-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Entrance to military service, permanent change of station, or deployment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a lease described in subparagraph (A) or (B) of subsection (b)(1) that provides for monthly payment of rent, termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective 30 days after the first date on which the next rental payment is due and payable after the date on which the notice under subsection (c) is delivered. In the case of any other lease described in subparagraphs (A) and (B) of subsection (b)(1) termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective on the last day of the month following the month in which the notice is delivered.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099104-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Stop movement orders","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a lease described in subsection (b)(1)(C), termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective on the date on which the requirements of subsection (c) are met for such termination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099105-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Lease of motor vehicles","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a lease described in subsection (b)(2), termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective on the day on which the requirements of subsection (c) are met for such termination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd2099106-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Arrearages and other obligations and liabilities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099107-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Leases of premises","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Rent amounts for a lease described in subsection (b)(1) that are unpaid for the period preceding the effective date of the lease termination shall be paid on a prorated basis. The lessor may not impose an early termination charge, but any taxes, summonses, or other obligations and liabilities of the lessee in accordance with the terms of the lease, including reasonable charges to the lessee for excess wear, that are due and unpaid at the time of termination of the lease shall be paid by the lessee.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd2099108-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Leases of motor vehicles","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Lease amounts for a lease described in subsection (b)(2) that are unpaid for the period preceding the effective date of the lease termination shall be paid on a prorated basis. The lessor may not impose an early termination charge, but any taxes, summonses, title and registration fees, or other obligations and liabilities of the lessee in accordance with the terms of the lease, including reasonable charges to the lessee for excess wear or use and mileage, that are due and unpaid at the time of termination of the lease shall be paid by the lessee.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd2099109-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rent paid in advance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Rents or lease amounts paid in advance for a period after the effective date of the termination of the lease shall be refunded to the lessee by the lessor (or the lessor’s assignee or the assignee’s agent) within 30 days of the effective date of the termination of the lease.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd209910a-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Relief to lessor","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Upon application by the lessor to a court before the termination date provided in the written notice, relief granted by this section to a servicemember may be modified as justice and equity require.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd209910b-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Misdemeanor","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any person who knowingly seizes, holds, or detains the personal effects, security deposit, or other property of a servicemember or a servicemember’s dependent who lawfully terminates a lease covered by this section, or who knowingly interferes with the removal of such property from premises covered by such lease, for the purpose of subjecting or attempting to subject any of such property to a claim for rent accruing subsequent to the date of termination of such lease, or attempts to do so, shall be fined as provided in title 18, or imprisoned for not more than one year, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd209910c-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd209910d-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/i/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Military orders","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “military orders”, with respect to a servicemember, means official military orders (including orders for separation or retirement), or any notification, certification, or verification from the servicemember’s commanding officer, with respect to the servicemember’s current or future military duty status.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd209910e-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/i/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ConUS","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “continental United States” means the 48 contiguous States and the District of Columbia.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd209910f-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3955/i/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Permanent change of station","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “permanent change of station” includes separation or retirement from military service.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd2099110-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-17/ch888"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1940, ch. 888","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 305, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/189/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–189, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/2848"},"text":"117 Stat. 2848","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/454/tVII/s704"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–454, title VII, § 704","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/3624"},"text":"118 Stat. 3624","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275, title III","children":[],"tail":", §§ 301, 303(b)(5), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2875"},"text":"124 Stat. 2875","children":[],"tail":", 2878; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/407/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–407, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/5373"},"text":"132 Stat. 5373","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/dA/tV"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, div. A, title V","children":[],"tail":", §§ 545, 546, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/1377"},"text":"133 Stat. 1377","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":"–(d), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/706"},"text":"134 Stat. 706","children":[],"tail":", 707; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tV/s549"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title V, § 549","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/3620"},"text":"134 Stat. 3620","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/tVII"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, title VII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 7201(a), 7202(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/5063"},"text":"134 Stat. 5063","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd2099111-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd2099112-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idd2099113-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to section 535 of the former Appendix to this title prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idd2099114-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 305 of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-10-17/ch888"},"text":"act Oct. 17, 1940, ch. 888","children":[],"tail":", art. III, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1942-10-06/ch581/s12"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1942, ch. 581, § 12","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/56/773"},"text":"56 Stat. 773","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/12/s9/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–12, § 9(9)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-03-18"},"text":"Mar. 18, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/40"},"text":"105 Stat. 40","children":[],"tail":", related to protection of assignor of life insurance policy, enforcement of storage liens, and penalties, prior to the general amendment of this Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/189"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–189","children":[],"tail":". See sections 3957 and 3958 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd2099115-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s549/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 549(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “The spouse or dependent of the lessee” for “The spouse of the lessee”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s549/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 549(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (4) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The spouse of the lessee on a lease described in subsection (b) may terminate the lease during the one-year period beginning on the date on which the lessee incurs a catastrophic injury or illness (as that term is defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s439/g"},"text":"section 439(g) of title 37","children":[],"tail":", if the lessee incurs the catastrophic injury or illness during a period of military service or while performing full-time National Guard duty, active Guard and Reserve duty, or inactive-duty training (as such terms are defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101/d"},"text":"section 101(d) of title 10","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1)(C)(ii), (2)(C)(ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/s7202/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, § 7202(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Secretary concerned” for “Secretary of Defense”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/315/s7201/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–315, § 7201(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2020—Subsec. (a)(1)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(c)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (1) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “In the case of a lease described in subsection (b)(1) that provides for monthly payment of rent, termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective 30 days after the first date on which the next rental payment is due and payable after the date on which the notice under subsection (c) is delivered. In the case of any other lease described in subsection (b)(1), termination of the lease under subsection (a) is effective on the last day of the month following the month in which the notice is delivered.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/158/s1/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–158, § 1(d)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of subsec. (i) by inserting “In this section:” before par. (1) without specifying the section being amended, was executed to subsec. (i) of this section, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s545/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 545(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “in subsection (b)” for “in subsection (b)(1)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s545/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 545(a)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s546/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 546(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “(including orders for separation or retirement)” after “official military orders”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s546/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 546(2)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/407/s301/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–407, § 301(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “by lessee” after “Termination” in heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/407/s301/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–407, § 301(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Termination by lessee” for “In general” in heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/407/s301/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–407, § 301(3)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275, § 301","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (e) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Rents or lease amounts unpaid for the period preceding the effective date of the lease termination shall be paid on a prorated basis. In the case of the lease of a motor vehicle, the lessor may not impose an early termination charge, but any taxes, summonses, and title and registration fees and any other obligation and liability of the lessee in accordance with the terms of the lease, including reasonable charges to the lessee for excess wear, use and mileage, that are due and unpaid at the time of termination of the lease shall be paid by the lessee.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/275/s303/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–275, § 303(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (h) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (h) related to penalties."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/454/s704/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–454, § 704(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (a) generally, designating existing provisions as p